    text "Philosophy of mind grapples with some of the most foundational questions in both philosophy and science: what is consciousness? What is the mind? How do mental states relate to physical processes in the brain? My work focuses on the debate between physicalism&#8212;the idea that mental states are reducible to brain states&#8212;and dual-aspect theories, which suggest that mind and brain are two perspectives on the same underlying reality"
